    "attributes": {
        "action": "For self employed new mums to not be discriminated against in the 80% gov help",
        "additional_details": "I understand this isn\u2019t a perfect system and the government is trying to help as many people as quickly as possible; but this oversight affects only women and that can\u2019t be right. \r\nAlso, self employed new mums make up a huge portion of ALL new mums. These women also can\u2019t now work from as no available childcare so everyone\u2019s income is virtually zero. (Can\u2019t teach from home with a baby/toddler!) Would be the right thing to do for all mothers and virtually impossible to abuse as there\u2019s birth records",
        "background": "when working out 80% of profits for the self employed over last 3 years, to take maternity time into account. The simplest way would be to not recognise the tax return for the year of giving birth, as this won\u2019t be a true representation of the profitability of the individual.Verify via birth records",
